 :tx/rationale "OUTPUT-AS-OBSERVATION — IMPLEMENTATION DESIGN: Three changes to the command pipeline. (1) In each knowledge-producing command's run function (task close, task create, transact, spec create), after building the result datoms but BEFORE writing the transaction, append auto-observation datoms to the SAME Vec<Datom>. The observation entity gets: :db/ident ':auto-obs/{command}-{tx_wall_time}', :exploration/body (the close reason or rationale string), :exploration/confidence (command-type inferred), :exploration/category ':exploration.cat/auto-command', :exploration/source (command name), :exploration/content-hash (BLAKE3 of body). (2) parse_spec_refs on the body text to extract INV-*/ADR-*/NEG-* references. For each resolved ref, add :exploration/related-spec Ref datom linking the auto-obs to the spec entity. This creates the graph edges that power spec_graph_neighbors and compile_demonstrations. (3) The auto-obs datoms are in the SAME transaction as the command's primary datoms — atomic, no extra IO, no cache invalidation. The per-command changes are ~5 lines each: extract body text (reason/rationale), call a shared auto_obs_datoms(body, command_name, tx) helper, append to datoms vec. CONSIDERATION: braid observe already creates explicit observations — auto-obs must NOT duplicate these. When the command IS observe, skip auto-obs (the explicit observation IS the output). Also skip for read-only commands (status, query, seed) since they don't produce write transactions."
